k between ZnS and CdS. TEM show that the particles are sphere and low distribution diameter in range of 3.4-6.1 nm. JSC and EFF% are 17.03 mA/cm2 and 5.87%, respectively.',NULL,'ZnCdS, solar cell, microwave irradiation, TEM',1,'O-01-024.doc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(151,372,'03','054',1,NULL,'This is How I Lose Her: Narrative Analysis of ‘Alma’  With a Focus on Style Shifting and Cultural Identity',NULL,'This paper made an attempt on narrative analysis of the piece ‘Alma’ in the short story collection This is How You Lose Her by Junot Díaz (2012). The analysis focuses on style shift and cultural identity while combining qualitative analysis and quantitative analysis. Drawing on the framework of Personal Experience Theory by Labov (2010) and the theory of Audience Design (Bell, 1984), this paper has discussed three aspects of its narrative strategies, and have found that in ‘Alma’, 1) the style of orientation tends to be relatively more informal while the resolution tends to be more formal; 2) the narrator and the protagonist may come to a relationship that is infinite close with the help of the abrupt style shift; 3) the use of intertextualized discourse drawing from both native Dominican discourse and immigrant-filtered discourse help discover the complex emotions depicted in the story and the cultural attitude of the narrator. The study shed light on analyzing literary discourse of writers with multicultural background as well as on the relationship among the protagonist, the narrator and the writer.',NULL,'literary linguistics; narrative analysis; discourse analysis; audience design; cultural identity',1,'O-03-054.docx','O-03-054.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'O-03-054.',1,2,0,0),(152,379,'03','055',1,NULL,'Communicating Goals: A Corpus-Assisted Analysis of Hotel Description Presented on Online Travel Agency Agoda',NULL,'The ultimate goal of the study is to investigate word choices of 4 and 5-star hotels that were advertised on the OTA, Agoda. A total of 97 hotel Overviews on the OTA Agoda were downloaded, prepared and examined using the corpus linguistics software, AntConc 3.5.8 (Anthony, 2019). The findings revealed 81 keywords with log likelihood values of at least 100 which are dominated by keywords relating to amenities, facilities and services (f=35; 43.21%), setting (f=24; 29.63%), and words relating to characteristic features of amenities, facilities and services (f=17; 20.99%), visitors (f=4; 4.94%) and involved production of language (f=1; 1.23%). These keywords depict that main role of the overviews on OTAs, i.e., to provide positively valued information about the services, amenities and facilities of the advertised hotels. Pedagogical implications of the study in the field of English for Specific Purposes as well as its methodological implications on the use of corpus-assisted analysis in the investigation of big data harnessed online were drawn.',NULL,'Agoda; Corpus-assisted analysis; Hotel overview; Keyword analysis; Online travel agent',1,'O-03-055.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'O-03-055.PNG',1,2,0,0),(153,136,'02','030',2,'การศึกษารวบรวมวิธีการรักษาจากกกรณีศึกษาในสมัยโบราณที่เกี่ยวข้องกับ ทฤษฎีความเศร้ากังวลทำลายปอด','The research and the management treatment methods from the ancient case record about the theory of Melancholy impairing lung','งานวิจัยนี้มีวัตถุประสงค์เพื่อศึกษารวบรวมข้อมูลการรักษาอาการหรือโรคที่มีสาเหตุตามทฤษฎี “อารมณ์เศร้ากังวลทำลายปอด” ของทางการแพทย์แผนจีน โดยใช้วิธีการสืบค้นรวบรวมข้อมูลจากแหล่งสารสนเทศ หนังสือบันทึกกรณีศึกษาในสมัยโบราณ คำสอนแพทย์แผนจีน และคัมภีร์โบราณทางการแพทย์แผนจีน สรุปรวบรวมวิธีการใช้ยาในการรักษาอาการหรือโรคที่มีสาเหตุตามแนวทางทฤษฎี “ความเศร้ากังวลทำลายปอด” ผลการศึกษาพบว่า ยาบำรุงปอดและม้าม และยาที่ผ่านเส้นลมปราณไตกับตับ ยาที่มีฤทธิ์อุ่น และยาที่มีรสหวานขม มีความถี่การใช้สูงที่สุด ส่วนยาฤทธิ์ร้อนมีความถี่ในการใช้ต่ำที่สุด โดยยาตังกุย หวงฉี และโสมคนซึ่งเป็นยาที่มีฤทธิ์บำรุงชี่และเลือดเป็นตัวยยาที่มีความถี่การใช้สูงที่สุด แสดงให้เห็นว่าหลักการใช้ยาในการรักษาอาการหรือโรคที่มีสาเหตุตามทฤษฎี “อารมณ์เศร้ากังวลทำลายปอด” ของทางการแพทย์แผนจีน ใช้หลักการ “รักษาปอดต้องปรับที่ม้าม” (ตามหลักปัญจธาตุม้ามเกิดปอด)  การใช้ยาอยู่บนพื้นฐานของการบำรุงชี่ เสริมม้ามเพิ่มพลังปอดปรับการไหลเวียนของชี่ บำรุงชี่เลือด และสลายเสมหะที่เกาะติดเป็นหลัก ผลการศึกษาสามารถใช้เป็นแนวทางในการรักษาอาการหรือโรคทางคลินิกที่เกิดจากสาเหตุดังกล่าวต่อไป','','แพทย์แผนจีน ความเศร้ากังวล ปอด','',1,'P-02-030.doc','P-02-030.doc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(154,392,'03','056',1,NULL,'Inclusive Education in the Philippines: Identifying Perceptions of Teachers',NULL,'Following the adoption and signing of the United Nations Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities, the Philippines agreed to follow the global trend of inclusive education (IE), but execution and implementation have been slow. Because teachers are the frontline for administering effective inclusive education practices, understanding their thoughts about such an education system is imperative. The SACIE-R Scale was administered to 313 elementary and secondary education and SPED teachers throughout three provinces in Region III of the Philippines. The aim was to identify the perspective of K-12 teachers on the implementation of inclusive education programs in schools in the Philippines, providing crucial information for developing more effective IE programs in the future. A CFA was performed and resulted in the removal of 3 variables. Based on the new 12 variable scale, the results indicated an average perception of 31.9, which signifies a neutral perception of IE. However, 46.3% of the participants weren’t familiar with inclusive education. Additionally, 64.5% of participants noted that they had no training for educating students with disabilities and amount of training was positively correlated with total SACIE-R score (r=.348, p< .001). This implies that teacher education and training should be a high priority moving forward. These findings can inform policy regarding the improvement of special education in the Philippines as well as provide insight into future training opportunities for pre-service and in-service teachers as the Philippines further attempts to adopt inclusive education practices. Further research is needed to identify perceptions nationwide.',NULL,'Inclusive Education; Special Education; Disability; Philippines; Teachers',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0),(155,417,'02','031',1,NULL,'The Case of Post-K12 Freshmen Nursing Students: Describing their Attributes and Understanding Links',NULL,'Determining the attributes of post-K12 freshmen nursing students and determining the associations that exists, through a descriptive-correlational research design, is essential in successful administration of the curriculum.  A total of 39 post-K12 freshmen nursing students, duly selected by consecutive-purposive sampling voluntarily answered the instruments, Dimensions of Learning, Readiness for Self-directed Learning and Approaches and Study Skills Inventory for Students (ASSIST). Results showed that post-K12 freshmen nursing students are mostly reflective observers that make use of the accommodative learning style. Analysis determined that the dimension of learning and learning style are linked statistically, hence, would mean that, accommodation is preceded by thoughtful reflective observation. They are adequately ready for self-directed learning that makes use of the deep approach to studying and possess the ability to reproduce and transform taught content and knowledge. Assessing the attributes of the learners is necessary in order to prepare a learning plan that is appropriate to address their needs.',NULL,'post-K12 freshmen nursing students, dimensions of learning, learning styles, self-directed learning, conception of learning, approaches to studying',1,'O-02-031.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'O-02-031.PNG',0,2,0,0),(157,398,'04','042',1,NULL,'the influence of computer anxiety and computer attitude on the expertise of computer users',NULL,'This research empirically examines the Effects of Computter Anxiety and the Effects of Computter Attitude on Expertise of Computer Users with Locus of Control (LoC) as a moderating variable in students of Accounting Study Program STIE AUB Surakarta. The research method used is path analysis which will be tested by Moderated Regression Analysis ( MRA). Data collection techniques using questionnaires, samples in this study were students of Accounting Study Program STIE AUB Surakarta who were taking accounting computer courses totaling 153 students. The results of the linearity test show R2 value of 0.225 with 153 observations, the value of c2 count = 153 x 0.235 = 35.96 while the c2 table value is 51.26. The value of c2 count <c2 table so it can be concluded that the correct model is a linear model. In the first hypothesis test Computer anxiety (β1) regression coefisian is 0.281829 meaningful if the computer anxiety variable has a positive relationship on the computer user expertise variable with the locus of control variable as moderation. On the second hypothesis test, computer attitude (β2) regression coeficiency is 1.237174 meaning if the computer attitude variable has a negative relationship on the computer user expertise variable with the locus of control variable as moderation. The use of LoC as a moderating variable for the Computter Anxiety dimension on the expertise of computer users of students of Accounting Study Program STIE AUBSurakarta is effective',NULL,'Computter Anxiety; Computter Attitude; locus of control and Computer User Skills',1,'O-04-042.docx','O-04-042.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'O-04-042.pdf',1,2,0,0),(159,397,'04','044',1,NULL,'Social Media Marketing Dimension in improving MSME Product Purchase Decisions in Boyolali Region with Innovation Ability as a Mediation Variable',NULL,'The aim of the study was to know empirically the influence of social media marketing dimensions on purchasing decisions that are expected to contribute positively in the form of strengthening theoretical views on the relationship between content creation, content sharing, connectivity and community bullying on innovation capabilities and purchasing decisions. The population in this study were all MSMEs in the Boyolali region that were registered at the Cooperative & SME Office of Boyolali Regency in January 2019. The samples studied were 190 respondents by multiplying the number of parameters, 19x10 = 190. The sampling technique uses random sampling. The analysis technique uses Structural Equation Modeling (SEM). The results show that content creation, content sharing, conneting and community bulding have a significant positive effect on innovation capabilities. Content creation and content sharing have a positive and insignificant effect on purchasing decisions. Conneting, community bulding and the ability of innovation have a significant positive effect on purchasing decisions. Indirect influence is greater than direct influence, so using innovation capability as a mediating variable is appropriate',NULL,'Content creation, Content sharing, Conecting, Community Building, Innovation Ability, Purchasing Decisions',1,'O-04-044.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(160,419,'04','045',1,NULL,'Individual Absorptive Capacity : Process Perspective of Technology Transfer in Surakarta Private University',NULL,'',NULL,'absorptive capacity, technology transfer, process perspective, individual level',1,'O-04-045.doc','O-04-045.doc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'O-04-045.pdf',1,2,0,0),(161,418,'04','046',1,NULL,'Immediate and Trend Changes of Composite Stock Index Based On Islamic Compared to National Calendar: Evidence from Indonesia',NULL,'This study investigates the trend of Indonesia stock composite index based on Islamic and National Calendar. The focus of this research is the trend of a composite index on the Islamic calendar during Ramadhan month. Month of Ramadhan is the important moment compared to other months in Indonesia. Moreover, Indonesia is the country with the largest Muslim population in the world. Ramadhan is placed at the beginning of the year to start stock investment predictions based on trends as the beginning of the national year which began in January. We analyzed historical data of Indonesia composite index. Data were analyzed by Interrupted Time Series Analysis. The results showed that immediate and trend changes occur in both of calendar based. This study provide consideration that Islamic calendar is indicated to be more reliable than national calendar to estimates long term investment decision of stock. Investor only need to pay attention at immediate changes based on critical event Islamic calendar. However, this estimation is not recommended if investors want to get abnormal returns. A greater opportunity to get abnormal returns and monthly return of stock will be obtained when using certain moment identification based on the national calendar.',NULL,'Islamic calendar; national; Indonesia composite index; immediately changing; slope',1,'O-04-046.docx','O-04-046.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'O-04-046.',1,2,0,0),(162,403,'04','047',1,NULL,'EMPOWERMENT OF  EMPLOYEES IN CREATIVE ECONOMIC BUSINESS : CASE STUDY ON SURAKARTA CITY',NULL,'',NULL,'Empowerment employee, economic creative',1,'O-04-047.docx','O-04-047.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'O-04-047.pdf',1,2,0,0),(163,423,'03','057',1,NULL,'Living with the Enemy: Violence in Light of Emmanuel Levinas’ Disinterested Responsibility',NULL,'This study attempts to understand the subtleties of hatred and violence by drawing from the insights of Emmanuel Levinas who recognizes the possibility of the legitimate use of violence for the sake of the natural dignity of the person and the inherent value of all persons. The paper examines Levinas’ disinterested responsibility which describes the ethical relation between the I and the Other. Secondly, it outlines carefully Levinas’ concept of justice which announces the entrance of the Third. Thirdly, it presents the conditions under which violence is justified and the constraints within which such measures can be introduced. Finally, it attempts to establish the connection between Levinasian concept of justice and the wisdom of forgiveness – an idea Levinas did not address directly in his philosophical works but which can be perceived as a valid response to honoring, rather than canceling out, justice.',NULL,'Disinterested Responsibility, Ethical Relation, Justice, Wisdom of Forgiveness ¬',1,'O-03-057.doc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'O-03-057.PNG',0,2,0,0),(164,425,'03','058',1,NULL,'Compliance, Commitment, and Challenges in the Implementation of Child Protection Policy in Bacolod City',NULL,'This study aimed to determine the compliance, commitment and challenges in the implementation of Child Protection Policy in Bacolod City. It sought to find out the extent of compliance and level of commitment of respondents in the areas of organizational sustainability, service delivery and community participation and when they are grouped according to age, sex, highest educational attainment, length of service, annual budgetary allocation, and location of the barangay.  Respondents were the 122 Barangay Captains and Council Chairmen of the Barangay Council for the Protection of Children (BCPC).  It utilized a validated and reliability-tested three-part self-made instrument consisting of the respondent’s profile, the 30-item questionnaire on the three (3) areas as well as the challenges encountered by barangay officials. Statistical tools such as frequency and percentage, mean, Mann-Whitney U Test, Kruskal-Wallis H-Test and Spearman Rho were used to analyze and interpret the data gathered.  \r\nFindings showed that the extent of compliance and the level of commitment of the respondents were “high”.  However, barangay officials who are younger, high school graduates with shorter length of service have “very high” extent of compliance. On the contrary, older barangay officials who are also high school graduates serving in urban barangays with higher annual budget allocation have “moderate” level of commitment.  \r\nThere is a significant difference in the extent of compliance of the barangay officials in the implementation of CPP when respondents were grouped and compared according age in the area of organizational sustainability; when grouped and compared according to annual budget allocation and location of barangay in service delivery; and when grouped and compared according age and highest educational attainment in community participation.  Likewise, there is a significant difference in the level of commitment of the barangay officials in the implementation of CPP when respondents are grouped and compared according to age, highest educational attainment, annual budget allocation and location of barangays in the area of organizational sustainability; when grouped and compared according to annual budget allocation and location of barangays in service delivery; and, when grouped and compared according to age and location of barangay in community participation. Nevertheless, there was significant relationship between the extent of compliance and the level of commitment of barangay officials in the implementation of CPP.  \r\nFinally, the top three (3) challenges encountered by the barangay officials were limited budgetary allocation of barangays for the operations of the BCPC; insufficient orientation of the duties and responsibilities of the committee members due to change in local leadership; and, incomplete orientation activities to strengthen BCPC.',NULL,'Child Protection Policy, Mann-Whitney U Test, Kruskal-Wallis H-Test, Spearman Rho, Organizational Sustainability.',1,'O-03-058.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'O-03-058.PNG',1,2,0,0),(165,426,'03','059',1,NULL,'Bridging the Notion of Intelligible Pronunciation in English and Positive Attitudes toward Learners’ Own English Accent',NULL,'This paper presents a part of literature review in relation to factors that affect English language learning and speaking. The review indicates research gap for a study the authors have been working since 2017. It was found that age, native language, language exposure, and attitude are recognized by scholars, researchers, and teachers as variables that determine the level and success of foreign/second language learning. Bridging the notion of intelligible pronunciation in English and positive attitudes toward learners’ own English accent may be suitable for a Thai social context. By taking such variables into account, the authors employed the phonetics website, a technology teaching tool, to teach English sounds that do not exist in Thai to non-English major undergraduate students so as to help them focus on clear pronunciation and promote their positive attitudes toward their own English accent.  The teaching tool is used as a means to help the students bridge the notion of clear pronunciation and their positive attitudes toward their own English accent.',NULL,'intelligible pronunciation in English; positive attitude; English accent; positive attitude toward one’s own English accent',1,NULL,'O-03-059.doc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'O-03-059.PNG',1,2,0,0),(166,438,'03','060',1,NULL,'English Language Teaching in Thailand from the Perspective of Bangkok Post: A Corpus-assisted Analysis',NULL,'The main goal of the study is to investigate the content of news reports on English Language Teaching (ELT) as communicated by Bangkok Post online. Informed by a corpus-based investigation of data, a total of 156 news reports on English Language Teaching (ELT), composed of 12187-word types and 209357-word tokens, were downloaded and prepared to be examined using the corpus linguistics software, AntConc 3.5.8 (Anthony, 2019). The findings revealed 71 keywords with log-likelihood values of at least 100 that were dominated by words relating to ELT and education matters (f=31; 43.66%), setting (f=11; 15.49%), ELT and education stakeholders (f=9; 12.68%), ELT and education physical structures and facilities (f=8; 11.27%), government concerns, offices and officials (f=6; 8.45%), production of language (f=5; 7.04%), and financial matters (f=1; 1.41%). These keywords depict the kinds information presented by the reporters of Bangkok Post online to their assumed readers. Implications on the use of corpus-assisted analysis in the investigation of ELT big data harnessed online were drawn.',NULL,'Bangkok Post online; Corpus-assisted analysis; English language teaching; Keyword analysis',1,'O-03-060.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(167,442,'03','061',1,NULL,'Coproducing a City of Difference: Integrating Indigeneity In Urban Strategic Spatial Planning',NULL,'This study focuses on land use planning dialectics in the Philippine Cordillera Administrative Region and how a theory of indigenous planning in highly urbanized areas can be formulated. It adopts the pre-theoretical stance that a radically new approach to spatial planning in an urbanized area where an indigenous people constitute a significant stakeholder segment of the population is urgently needed. \r\nThrough a qualitative approach, the study establishes that (1) the current state planning paradigm is rational-comprehensive, aligning the city plan to higher level plans; (2) this paradigm leads to theoretical contradictions manifested in discordances in roles and identities, capacities, and agential-specific performances; (3) these discordances, in turn, echo in the tridimensional theme consisting of people (issues on identity and roles lead to the exclusion of indigenous peoples from land use planning), power (laws  limit indigenous participation and involvement), and process (planning constrain participative involvement outside the structures of power).\r\nThe study concludes that the integration of indigeneity into strategic spatial planning can be accomplished through a coproduction approach using a temporally-sustained relational negotiation process. Three coproduction scenarios are spelled out for implementational purposes. The study also concludes that the planning process itself coproduced. For the indigenous, planning does not merely entail economic considerations that look at space as resource to be utilized. Planning is an inversion. It makes the indigenous – not space – the center of the planning process.',NULL,'strategic spatial planning; indigenous peoples; ancestral lands; coproduction; urban planning',1,'O-03-061.docx','O-03-061.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(168,443,'03','062',1,NULL,'Predictive Success in Criminology Licensure Examinations through Academic Performance on: Implications on Program Development',NULL,'Higher educational institutions (HEIs), through their programs in criminology, have been increasingly contributive to the development and professionalization of the national police and the state’s criminal justice system. Indeed, such professionalization and development has been the goal of the state ever since the passage of Republic Act 6506, otherwise known as “An Act Creating the Board of Examiners for Criminologists in the Philippines and for Other Purposes” on July 1, 1972.  In furtherance of this goal, albeit belatedly, the Philippine Commission on Higher Education (CHED) issued CHED Memorandum Order 21, series of 2005 thirty three years later , laying down the policies and standards to be followed for the criminology program in HEIs. The vision of these issuances, of course, is to mold a professional corps of police officers dedicated to protect and to serve the citizenry; their mission is to enable the criminology graduate to pass the licensure examinations for professional criminologists.',NULL,'Academic performance; Criminology licensure examinations; Predictive success; Program development',1,'O-03-062.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(169,444,'05','007',1,NULL,'Local Community Assessment on the Environmental Impacts of Ecotourism at Tangadan Falls, San Gabriel, La Union',NULL,'Ecotourism will always have significant positive or negative impacts on the social, economic and environmental dimensions of the host community, in general. The study attempts to identify these ecotourism impacts specifically within the environmental realms of the waterfalls ecosystem. Quantitative data assessment of species diversity and water quality were done in order to generate baseline data for relevant measurements of ecosystem indicators. Questionnaires were floated to gather qualitative data especially on the perception of stakeholders toward environmental concerns. Since the site is still an area for development, results are expected to yield baseline data which can be used for assessment and recommendation of possible conservation measures to prevent degradation of the water quality and immediate environment of the site. Based from the results, the disturbance brought by the influx of tourism can be reduced by efficient environmental management, planning, orientation and integration of scientific knowledge on the local community, tour operators, all tourists, local government units, and all other existing stakeholders within the area towards proper protection and conservation of freshwater ecosystems.',NULL,'Ecotourism; Conservation; Management',1,'O-05-007.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,2,0,0),(170,447,'03','063',1,NULL,'Research Involvement of Faculty Members and Staff at Panpacific University: Basis for a University Research Development Plan',NULL,'It is undeniable that research is an essential part and function of a higher education institution (HEI). In fact, research is considered as a backbone of global university ranking and its outcomes, specifically based on research productivity or quality. This is important to note as it could enable a university to uphold quality and its function by showing evidence of research productivity, quality, and capability. This research study aimed to look into the faculty members and non-teaching staffs’ strengths, struggles and other factors that affect their involvement in conducting research. The researchers made use of a quantitative research design to gather data with a focus group discussion as a supplement in knowing their competencies, attitude and difficulties in research. Three adapted questionnaires are the Research Competencies Scale (RCS), Attitude Towards Research (ATR) and Research Difficulty Questionnaires (RDQ) which were used in gathering the data. The findings of the study showed that the faculty members and non-teaching staffs showed an average level of research competencies, moderate level of attitude towards research and does find research as difficult.',NULL,'Attitude, competencies, difficulty, faculty, non-teaching, research',1,'O-03-063.docx','O-03-063.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(172,445,'01','025',1,NULL,'Water-Quality Assessment of Dipalo River in San Quintin, Pangasinan through Physico-chemical Parameters and Macrobenthos',NULL,'Macroinvertebrates are commonly used as bioindicators because they can provide information on environmental condition due to sensitivity of single species. This study presented a water quality assessment of Dipalo River to provide a baseline study regarding the health status of the river. Physico-chemical parameters such as temperature, conductivity, dissolved oxygen, pH, phosphates and flow rate were measured. And there were significant differences observed among physico-chemical parameters in relation to sampling months. The mean temperature, dissolved oxygen, and pH were within the DENR required level of water quality parameters under Class C.  Furthermore, macrobenthos collected using surber sampler method was dominated by family Perlidae (25%), Odontoceridae (16%) and Heptageniidae (13%). Calculated Family Biotic Index (2.19) and Average Score per Taxon (7.71) suggested that there is no organic pollution in the area, and has a good to excellent water quality.',NULL,'Macrobenthos; Family Biotic Index; Average Score per Taxon',1,'O-01-025.docx','O-01-025.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(173,449,'03','065',1,NULL,'Reading Literacy:  Predictor of Academic Achievement',NULL,'Premised on  the constructivist theory of learning,  this paper attempts to explore the relationship between  reading proficiency and academic success. A focused group discussion participated by teachers in a private school in Central Luzon was conducted to draw responses based on anecdotal accounts of classroom experiences and performance assessments of grade seven students who scored below the reading proficiency test for incoming junior high school students.\r\n\r\n	A focused group discussion interview guide, validated by content experts in the field of English language learning and reading, was utilized in the interview. The FGD analysis yielded to results supporting  a direct correlation between reading literacy and academic achievement. On the basis of the findings of the research, it can be concluded that reading literacy is a predictor of academic success. Moreover, results suggest that a variety of exposure to reading opportunities may increase the chances of students to perform better in  various academic disciplines.  Hence, this study recommends to provide a self-paced reading comprehension learning module to facilitate mastery of reading strategies which may support in elevating mastery of reading comprehension skills and improve overall academic performance.',NULL,'reading proficiency, academic success, comprehension',1,'O-03-065.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(174,452,'03','066',1,NULL,'Interfacing Whole Child Approach and the Comer School Development Program:  Addressing the low academic performance of students',NULL,'Schools focus on the revision of the curriculum to address concerns on the non-performance of the students academically. More often than not, non-academic performance is not equated to emotional and social instability, therefore, the curriculum the schools design is not designed to address this concern. In this paper, an interface between whole child approach and Comer School Development Program will be used to level up the academic performance of the students which is a result of activities conducted that pays attention to the following tenets of the whole child: healthy, supported, challenged, engaged and safe. These tenets will be used in the preparation of the school development program of Comer which involves the whole school community: from the principal, teachers, to the support staff and parents. The school development program is that which will be used in the revision of the school curriculum to address the low academic performance of the students.',NULL,'Comer School Development Program; Low Academic Performance Students Whole Child Approach',1,'O-03-066.doc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(175,370,'02','032',1,NULL,'Factors Correlated to Nursing Practice Stress among 3rd. year of Nursing Students in Private University',NULL,'The purpose of this research was to study the factors related to stress of 3rd. year of Nursing Students in Private University. The sampling was 122 of Nursing Students from the Faculty of Nursing. The research instrument was the questionnaires include demographic, social and educational information and Suan Prung stress measurement (SPST - 20) from Department of Mental Health. The data were collected and analyzed statistic results by using The Pearson Product Moment Correlation Coefficient. \r\nThe finding found that sex, Practical courses and education factor correlated to students’ stress on Nursing student. The researchers suggested that students should have an activity to reduce the stress by exchanging students’ experience between junior and senior students for stress improvement. Moreover, junior students who don’t undergo the nursing practicing should be provided advice, knowledge, and experience exchange on nursing practicing',NULL,'stress, Nursing Students, practical nursing',1,'O-02-032.doc','O-02-032.doc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(177,471,'03','067',1,NULL,'Who Pays the Price of Incarceration? – Impact of Paternal Incarceration to the Shadows of Prison',NULL,'This paper summarizes the lived experiences of the family of an incarcerated father also known as the shadows of prison. This study used the qualitative approach through a narrative inquiry employing in-depth interview as the main data gathering tool. It was revealed that paternal incarceration greatly disturbs family relations. Its impact includes having marital strain, distress on the part of the wife who is concerned about the safety of her incarcerated husband, absence of a father figure in the family resulting to children’s neglect, financial burden, social stigma and emotional tensions. The findings of the study will motivate and empower the inmates and their family members to cope up with the challenges they are facing through an understanding of the impacts of paternal incarceration. Further, this study will help the readers to realize the situation of the inmate’s family members and be of help in their recovery.',NULL,'paternal incarceration; shadows of prison; impact of incarceration; problems of separation',1,'O-03-067.docx','O-03-067.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(178,470,'02','033',1,'ปัจจัยที่มีความสัมพันธ์ต่อความเครียดของนักศึกษาชั้นปีที่ 4 คณะสาธารณสุขศาสตร์และสิ่งแวดล้อม มหาวิทยาลัยหัวเฉียวเฉลิมพระเกียรติ','Factors on Stress of Students 4 th the Public Health and Environment at Huachiew Chalermprakiet University','การศึกษาวิจัยในครั้งนี้เป็นการวิจัยเชิงพรรณนา แบบภาคตัดขวางมีวัตถุประสงค์เพื่อศึกษาปัจจัยที่มีความสัมพันธ์ต่อความเครียดของนักศึกษาชั้นปีที่ 4 คณะสาธารณสุขศาสตร์และสิ่งแวดล้อม มหาวิทยาลัยหัวเฉียวเฉลิมพระเกียรติ โดยใช้กลุ่มตัวอย่าง จานวน 165 คน เครื่องมือที่ใช้เป็นแบบสอบถามซึ่งประกอบไปด้วยข้อมูล 4 ส่วน ได้แก่ ข้อมูลส่วนบุคคล ข้อมูลด้านปัจจัยการเรียน ข้อมูลระดับความสุขและข้อมูลระดับความเครียด โดยนาไปทดสอบหาความเชื่อมั่นได้ ค่าแอลฟ่าคอนบราคเท่ากับ 0.86 สถิติที่ใช้ได้แก่ จานวน ความถี่ ร้อยละ ค่าเฉลี่ย ไคส-แควร์ \r\nผลการวิจัยพบว่ากลุ่มตัวอย่างส่วนใหญ่เป็นเพศหญิงร้อยละ 91.5 และเพศชายร้อยละ 8.5 ส่วนใหญ่อายุ 22 ปี ร้อยละ 58.8 มีค่าดัชนีมวลกาย (BMI) อยู่ในเกณฑ์ปกติ ส่วนใหญ่เป็นนักศึกษาสาขาการจัดการโรงพยาบาล ร้อยละ 45.5 มีผลการเรียน 6 เทอม(GPA) ระหว่าง 2.51-3.00 ร้อยละ 41.2 มีรายรับของนักศึกษาต่อเดือน ระหว่าง 3,001-6,000 บาท ร้อยละ 41.2 ส่วนใหญ่มีสถานภาพครอบครัว บิดา-มารดาอยู่ด้วยกัน ร้อยละ 73.3 ระยะเวลานอนส่วนใหญ่ 4-9 ชั่วโมง ร้อยละ 48.5 ระยะในการเรียน 4-6 ชั่วโมง ร้อยละ 59.4 ส่วนใหญ่ไม่สูบบุหรี่ ร้อยละ 96.4 ไม่ดื่มเครื่องดื่มแอลกอฮอล์ ร้อยละ 76.4 ไม่ออกกาลังกาย ร้อยละ 44.2 ลักษณะการเรียนที่มีผลต่อความเครียดส่วนใหญ่คือทฤษฎี/บรรยาย+ปฏิบัติ ร้อยละ 44.2 และมีช่องทางในการสื่อสาร รับข่าวสาร ส่วนใหญ่ คือ ไลน์ ร้อยละ 97.6 ปัจจัยด้านการเรียนที่ส่วนใหญ่ทาให้เกิดความเครียดน้อย ร้อยละ 71.5 และกลุ่มตัวอย่างส่วนใหญ่มีระดับความเครียดสูงกว่าปกติเล็กน้อย ร้อยละ 36.4 จากผลการวิเคราะห์หาความสัมพันธ์ พบว่า ปัจจัยที่มีความสัมพันธ์ต่อความเครียดของนักศึกษาชั้นปีที่ 4 คณะสาธารณสุขศาสตร์และสิ่งแวดล้อม มหาวิทยาลัยหัวเฉียวเฉลิมพระเกียรติ คือ ปัจจัยส่วนบุคคล ปัจจัยด้านการเรียนไม่มีความสัมพันธ์กับระดับความเครียดที่ P-value > 0.05 เนื่องจากนักศึกษาส่วนใหญ่มีช่วงอายุไม่แตกต่างกันมากมีการกระจายของข้อมูลน้อย ทุกสาขาวิชาเรียนหลักสูตร 4 ปี มีเนื้อหาและหน่วยกิตที่ใกล้เคียงกัน มีความกังวลเรื่องผลการเรียนจึงทำให้มีความเครียดไม่แตกต่างกัน','This study is the cross-section descriptive study which objective to study Factors on Stress of Public Health and Environment at Huachiew Chalermprakiet University. The sample group includes 165 people. The methods which is used for this study is questionnaire 4 Part 1.) personal information for learning. 2.) factor learning. 3.)level happiness. 4.) level stress. The test result of the reliability using Cronbach’s Alpha show that the reliability is 0.86. The descriptive statistics are frequency, percentage, mean and Chi-square. \r\nThe research found that Most of the sample has female 91.5 percent and has male 22 percent. Most of them had a body mass index (BMI) within the normal ranges. The majority of the students in hospital management, with 45.5 percent of grade 6 semesters (GPA) between 2:51 to 3:00, revenue were 41.2 percent of students between 3001-6000 baht per month, 41.2 percent of a family\'s status. Father - and mother living together, 73.3 percent of the time sleep 4-9 hours in length, 48.5 percent to 59.4 percent, mostly 4-6 hours, not smoking, not drinking alcohol, 96.4 percent, 76.4 percent did not exercise. 44.2 percent of physical characteristics that affect learning, stress are mostly theoretical / practical lectures: 44.2 percent and channels of communication most news is line application 97.6 percent of the class. Causing the most stress and strain at 71.5 percent and the stress levels are slightly above normal at 36 percent. 4. The results of the analysis showed that the correlation factor is related to the stress of the 4th year student of the Faculty of Public Health and Environment. To conclude the personal factor. Factors Study and happiness levels did not correlate with stress levels that P-value> 0.05. Because the sample group age isn\'t very different. There is little information on the distribution of all sample are subject to 4 years course. Content and credits at nearby. There are concerns the effects of learning stress makes no difference','นักศึกษาชั้นปีที่ 4 คณะสาธารณสุขศาสตร์และสิ่งแวดล้อม','learning stress makes no difference',1,'O-02-033.doc','O-02-033.doc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(179,99,'02','034',1,'ความสัมพันธ์ระหว่างการใช้สมาร์ทโฟนกับสุขภาพจิตของนักศึกษามหาวิทยาลัยหัวเฉียวเฉลิมพระเกียรติ','Relationship between Smartphone Usages and Mental Health in Huachiew Chalermprakiet University Students','การวิจัยภาคตัดขวาง (Cross – sectional study) ครั้งนี้มีวัตถุประสงค์เพื่อศึกษาความสัมพันธ์ระหว่างการใช้สมาร์ทโฟนกับสุขภาพจิตในกลุ่มนักศึกษามหาวิทยาลัยหัวเฉียวเฉลิมพระเกียรติชั้นปีที่ 1-4 ทั้ง 13 คณะ จำนวน 404 คน เครื่องมือที่ใช้ในการวิจัยคือ แบบสอบถามข้อมูลส่วนบุคคล อาการเสพติดสมาร์ทโฟน และแบบทดสอบสุขภาพจิต ซึ่งมีค่าสัมประสิทธิ์แอลฟาของคอนบราค (Cronbach\'s alpha coefficient) 0.75 และ 0.84 ตามลำดับ วิเคราะห์ข้อมูลด้วยสถิติเชิงพรรณนาและสถิติไคสแควร์\r\nผลการวิจัย พบว่า ร้อยละ 64.85 เป็นเพศหญิง มีอายุเฉลี่ย 20.51 ± 1.37 ปี ร้อยละ 45.05 มีการเข้าใช้สมาร์ทโฟนเฉลี่ย 15-20 ครั้งต่อวัน ร้อยละ 46.29  มีการใช้งานเฉลี่ยมากกว่า 5 ชั่วโมงต่อวัน แอปพลิเคชันที่นิยมใช้มากที่สุดคือ อินสตาแกรม (Instagram) และการเสพติด\r\nสมาร์ทโฟนมีความสัมพันธ์กับสุขภาพจิต (p =.001) เพื่อภาวะสุขภาพจิตที่ดี นักศึกษาจึงควรลดการเสพติดสมาร์ทโฟนลง','This cross-sectional research aims to study the relationship between smartphone usages and mental health in Huachiew Chalermprakiet University students. The student sample consisted of 404 who studying in the first to forth year from 13 faculties. Research tool used in this study was a questionnaire of personal information and smartphone addiction, and mental health test. The Cronbach\'s alpha coefficient of the questionnaire and the mental health test was 0.75 and 0.84, respectively. Data were analyzed using descriptive statistics and Chi Square test.\r\nThe results showed that 64.85 percent was female, the average age was 20.51 ± 1.37 years, 45.05 percent have the average number of times to smartphone usages in \r\na day in the range of 15 to 20 times, 46.29 percent have the average time spent on \r\na smartphone using over 5 hours per day, the most popular application was Instagram, and smartphone addiction was significantly associated with the mental health of students (p =.001). For good mental health, students should reduce smartphone addiction','สมาร์ทโฟน การเสพติดสมาร์ทโฟน สุขภาพจิต','Smartphone, smartphone  addiction, mental health',1,'O-02-034.doc','O-02-034.doc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(180,108,'02','035',1,'ปัจจัยที่มีความสัมพันธ์ต่อภาวะซึมเศร้าในกลุ่มนักศึกษามหาวิทยาลัยหัวเฉียวเฉลิมพระเกียรติ','Associated Factors of Depression in Hauchiew Chalermprakiet University Students','การวิจัยภาคตัดขวาง (Cross – Sectional Study) ครั้งนี้มีวัตถุประสงค์เพื่อศึกษาปัจจัยที่มีความสัมพันธ์กับภาวะซึมเศร้าในกลุ่มนักศึกษามหาวิทยาลัยหัวเฉียวเฉลิมพระเกียรติ \r\nกลุ่มตัวอย่างคือ นักศึกษามหาวิทยาลัยหัวเฉียวเฉลิมพระเกียรติชั้นปีที่ 1-4 ทั้ง 13 คณะ จำนวน 397 คน เครื่องมือที่ใช้ในการวิจัยคือ แบบสอบถามข้อมูลส่วนบุคคล ปัจจัยด้านอื่น ๆ และแบบประเมินภาวะซึมเศร้าของเบค (Beck Depression Inventory – II) ซึ่งมีค่าสัมประสิทธิ์แอลฟาของคอนบราค (Cronbach\'s alpha coefficient) 0.91 และ 0.87 ตามลำดับ วิเคราะห์ข้อมูลด้วยสถิติเชิงพรรณนาและสถิติไคสแควร์ \r\nผลการวิจัย พบว่า ร้อยละ 76.32 เป็นเพศหญิง มีอายุเฉลี่ย 20.20 ± 1.66 ปี ร้อยละ 44.08 มีภาวะซึมเศร้า และปัจจัยที่มีความสัมพันธ์กับภาวะซึมเศร้าคือ ปัญหาการเรียน ปัญหาความรัก ปัญหาการนอน ปัญหาเศรษฐกิจและสังคม และปัญหาด้านสิ่งแวดล้อม (p <.001) จึงเสนอให้ลดปัจจัยที่เสี่ยงต่อการเกิดภาวะซึมเศร้า','This cross-sectional research aims to study factors that associated with the depression in Hauchiew Chalermprakiet University (HCU) students. The student sample consisted of 397 who studying in the first to forth year from 13 faculties. Research tool used in this study was a questionnaire of personal information and other factors, and the evaluation of beck\'s depression inventory-II. The Cronbach\'s alpha coefficient of the questionnaire and the evaluation form was 0.91 and 0.87, respectively. Data were analyzed using descriptive statistics and Chi Square test.\r\nThe results showed that 76.32 percent was female, the average age was 20.20 ± 1.66 years, 44.08 percent of participant had depression, and factors that associated with the depression were learning problems, sleep problems, love problems, economic and social issues, and environmental issues (p <.001). Therefore, this study suggests that risk factors for depression should be reduced','ภาวะซึมเศร้า ความชุก นักศึกษา','Depression, prevalence, students',1,'O-02-035.doc','O-02-035.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(181,494,'03','068',1,NULL,'Interpersonal Communication Style between Doctors and Their Patients: A Case Study of XYZ Hospital in Bogor, Indonesia',NULL,'Effective communication between doctors and patients is very important and necessary. Patients come to the hospital to consult a doctor about the disease. The patient hopes to get a detailed explanation from the doctor and the disease can be treated. Good interpersonal communication between doctors and patients makes patients feel comfortable and at ease. A comfortable feeling can help patients recover more optimally and quickly. There are two forms of interpersonal communication orientations used, namely the doctor-oriented interpersonal communication style and patient-oriented interpersonal communication style. This research is a qualitative descriptive study conducted on doctors A, B and C at XYZ Hospital, Bogor. The aim of the study was to determine the interpersonal communication style of doctors and patients that were related to the tendency of patients to choose a doctor if they were treated. The results showed that the doctor\'s interpersonal communication style that was hoped by the patients was doctor A, compared to doctor B, and C. Doctor A had a patient-oriented interpersonal communication style, while doctors B and C had a doctor-oriented communication style. Doctors are expected not only to act as people who provide diagnosis and treat diseases but also can provide spiritual motivation, enthusiasm for patients, and empathize with the condition.',NULL,'Interpersonal communication style, doctor and patients; spirituality',1,'O-03-068.docx','O-03-068.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(182,495,'03','069',1,NULL,'Implementation of Chain of Custody on Public Service Administration in Indonesia',NULL,'Administrative processes can be seen through a general process, while administrative action can be examined at a certain program level. Chain of custody (CoC), in the context of law, refers to chronological documentation or paper traces that record the sequence of detention, control, transfer, analysis, and disposition of physical or electronic evidence. In the service process, the CoC serves to track service documents or document traces according to the procedures specified. In public services, administrative activities are carried out to control the efforts of government agencies so that their objectives are achieved. This paper aims to examine the application of CoC to the administration of public services in Indonesia. Based on the quasi-qualitative approach taken, it was produced that the application of CoC to the administration of public services can provide a useful framework for understanding and improving efforts to reduce administrative problems in public services.',NULL,'Chain of Custody / CoC, administration, public services',1,'O-03-069.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(183,503,'03','070',1,NULL,'A Critical Look at the Concept of the Learning Organization',NULL,'The purpose of this paper is to determine the conditions under which the principles of the Learning Organization cannot (or should not) be applied. On a broader scale, this paper explores recent models of organizational development and change, which have dampened the luster of the concept of the learning organization, making it only one of many tools for the organizational development practitioner. For the subject expert, this review offers possible approach for critical review and the selection of subject content during curriculum development.',NULL,'Learning organization, Organizational culture model',1,'O-03-070.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,2,0,0),(184,18,'01','026',1,NULL,'ทดสอบ',NULL,'ทดสอบ2',NULL,'ทดสอบ',1,'O-01-026.docx',NULL,'O-01-026.docx','O-01-026.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,2,0,0),(