entify that the use of this technique is advantage.\r\n- Too short discussion, there were no reasons to explain the effect of the technique.','Introduction: No detail for objective of study. It just only review literature.\r\nDiscussion: No explanation the reason of this result. It just only the same introduction','It was identified in the conclusion of the study that there were some side effects from the use of Thai traditional massage, but the title of the study stated that this technique is safety. Therefore, dose it safe or not safe from using of this technique?','',4,1),(86,32,314,1,8,20,30,13,8,'','','','','',3,1),(87,59,314,1,8,20,30,15,8,'','','','','',2,1),(88,175,463,1,8,20,30,10,8,'','','','','',3,1),(89,160,284,2,8,20,32,12,8,'Good','Good','Good','very good','Good',2,1),(90,162,271,2,10,20,30,10,7,'','','1. Writing . “the introduction section” should quote more sources of information.\r\n2. The source of the information should be information during the year. 2013-2019 (if possible).\r\n3. The data analysis should be added in terms of whether the results of studies are consistent or inconsistent with previous research','Should add to the summary the important points of all parameters (desire, trust, confident, creditability, accountability, communication).','Many sources of information are not mentioned  in the reference. (for example, Dessler, 2015; Walton, 2002).',3,1),(91,144,458,1,7,15,15,7,4,'','','','','',4,1),(92,169,476,1,8,20,19,7,5,'The topic is clear and reflects the goal of the research study.','The abstract should be revised to include the findings.\r\nGrammar should be corrected.','The author wrote \"Ecotourism ideally aims to have a low impact on the environment, contribute to the local economy, engender cross- cultural exchange and foster environmental education and in many ways, it has many advantages compared to tourism.\" The author is laying the foundation of the research, so citations are needed here.\r\n\r\nThe author wrote \"Ecotourism will always have significant positive or negative impacts on the social, economic and environmental dimensions of the host community, in general.\" What are some known +/- impacts. The author should unpack this a bit.\r\n\r\nThe author wrote \"Tangadan falls, situated within sitio Amontoc, Barangay Tangadan in the town of San Gabriel in La Union Province, is one of the ecotourism spots being popularized in the area and is very accessible for tourists and travelers visiting the surfing capital of the Philippines -- San Juan, La Union.\" What makes Tangadan Falls located in San Juan, La Union interesting to study? This information is crucial since there are hundreds of waterfalls in the area (of La Union and in the Philippines) and only one site was chosen by the researcher. The research should also unpack the context of the research. \r\n\r\nThe author wrote \"...there has been very little researches done on inland... Research in this context is uncountable.\r\n\r\n\"Further, the Millennium Ecosystem Assessment (MEA) in 2005 stated that they are among the most threatened ecosystems in the world.\" Include a reference.\r\n\r\n\"The collected macroinvertebrates were then studied under a microscope.\" Macroinvertebrates are visible to the naked eye. Why is there a need to use a microscope? What were studied under the microspcope?\r\n\r\n\"The instrument was divided into four parts namely: a.) Profile; b.) Knowledge; c.) Attitude; and d.) Practices.\" The reader is quite adamant on the validity of the instrument. The perceptions of stakeholders on the impacts of ecotourism were not asked. While it is plausible to generate insights from the responses of the participants in (c) and (d), directly asking the stakeholders of the impacts is more straightforward.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe title of the research study, \"Local Community Assessment on the Environmental Impacts of Ecotourism at Tangadan Falls, San Gabriel, La Union\" assumes that the locals are given the chance to assess the impacts of Ecotourism in the area. This was confirmed by the objective of the study, \"This study aims to identify the impacts of ecotourism within the Tangadan Falls ecosystem and recommend conservation measures that should be put in places before it becomes officially established tourist destination\". This objective is noble and worth examining. However, the instruments in gathering data (questionnaire) failed to gather data that shed light on the objectives.\r\n\r\nPut another way, the reader did not find these impacts in the manuscript. This is mainly due to faulty data gathering. Identifying the impacts using ocular investigation of biological biodiversity in the area is fine but the output or findings must be interpreted and synthesize  in a way that the impacts (+/-) stand out. The reader is left in quandary about what happened to the interview results. The impacts identified in the interview process (if any) are yet to be reported.','The discussion and conclusion are very simplistic and do not give due justice to the objective of the study.','There were a lot of grammatical inconsistencies. For instance, the author kept using \"based from\" instead of \"based on\". There several comma splices\r\nSome citations were not in the reference list and vice-versa.\r\nThe author should format the citations and references using APA 6th ed style.\r\nThe author should request an English language teacher or expert or a native English speaker to edit the language.',3,1),(93,45,322,1,8,8,8,8,8,'','','','','',2,1),(94,45,323,2,8,8,8,8,8,'','','','','',2,1),(95,172,491,2,7,15,15,7,8,'1. It is interesting topic but it is not clarity of the results.','1. Add the time of sampling collection in abstract.\r\n2. Recheck some macroinvertebrates ex. Odontoceridae (it may be Hydropsychidae: in figure 1 (b))\r\n3. Abstract: it should clarify relationship between water quality and macroinvertebrates.','1. Add more information of Macrobenthos species  used as  bioindicators. \r\n2.