,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'-Informed by a Levinasian concept disinterested responsibility the author keenly argued and shed some light on the fine nuances of hatred and violence specifically among humans who legitimately use violence for the sake of the natural dignity. The author could have enriched and explored further the arguments if related studies employing Levinas\' concepts were included in the discussions (see for example Gaston (2003)Gaston, S. (2003). https://academic.oup.com/litthe/article-abstract/17/4/407/970163?redirectedFrom=fulltext\r\n\r\n-Please make sure the references section follows APA 6th edition format.\r\n\r\nDECISION: Accept with minor revision.\r\n\r\nIMPORTANT: \r\n-The name, email, bionote and other information about the author were removed during the double blind review process. Please kindly return them prior to sending the final draft.\r\n-The final draft should be uploaded on the website using the author’s username and password NOT LATER THAN JUNE 10, 2019.',NULL,'O-03-057.docx',0),(159,164,162,NULL,NULL,NULL,165,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'1 Clarity of the topic\r\n\r\n-Not really certain what the purpose is except to check commitment based on variables. Perhaps explain further why it is important to know these as far as CPP is concerned.\r\n\r\n 2 Well-written abstract that includes all salient point of the article\r\n\r\n-Write (CPP) beside spelled out Child Protection Policy in the abstract; Use gender-sensitive words like Chairperson instead of Chairmen; \r\n\r\n3 Introduction and sections that discusses the details of the article\r\n\r\n-Introduction should be edited because it includes instructions of the template given by host of the conference. Add a line or two to explain how the findings will benefit a better implementation of the CPP. Is there a possibility to shorten the results and to just put the very important tables? Other findings can just be summarized.\r\n\r\n 4 Discussion and Conclusion\r\n-Given the significant difference, what is the implication? Must people vote for younger persons, females, college grads or whatever it is that show higher commitment?\r\n\r\n5 Use of appropriate citation and references with correct format\r\n-To be checked by the editor. \r\n\r\nOTHER COMMENTS:\r\n1. The manuscript is too long. The manuscript should NOT be more than 15 pages including the references and abstract. The reviewers suggest that the paper focuses on 2 to 3 objectives NOT 9. \r\n2. References and citations should match.\r\n3. The Appendices can be deleted in the final manuscript.\r\n\r\nIMPORTANT:\r\n-The final draft should be uploaded to the conference website not later than Sunday,  16th  June 2019.\r\n-The author should send a file explaining how each of the comments has been addressed. See the attached file.\r\n-The author should send the revision note to any of the following emails: hcu.epc@gmail.com; jrc.hcu@gmail.com','O-03-058.docx','O-03-058.docx',0),(160,165,430,NULL,NULL,NULL,364,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'1. What is being \"bridged\"?\r\n2. Include source/s on studies as regards variables affecting ESL/EFL learning.\r\n3. Although included in the abstract, the phonetic website, a technology teaching tool, was not discussed in the paper.\r\n4. Synthesis of the literature review was quite weak\r\n5. Second paragraph of Conclusion includes discussion of \"phonetic website\" which was not discussed in the introduction and literature review.\r\n6. Include retrieval dates for online sources\r\n\r\nIMPORTANT: \r\n-The name, email, bionote and other information about the author were removed during the double blind review process. Please kindly return them prior to sending the final draft.\r\n-The final draft should be uploaded on the website using the author’s username and password.\r\n-The author should send a file explaining how each of the comments has been addressed. See the attached file.\r\n\r\n-The author should send the revision note to:\r\nhcu.epc@gmail.com','O-03-059.docx','O-03-059.docx',0),(161,166,183,NULL,NULL,'O-03-060-1.docx',364,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'DECISION: ACCEPT WITH MINOR REVISIONS\r\n\r\n1. Topic\r\nThe research topic is clear and the goal of the study is clearly stated.\r\n2. Abstract\r\nThe abstract is well -written. The author clearly described objective of the study and briefly discussed research methodology, main findings and implications. However, the figures and percentages of keywords in some themes (educational matters, ELT and education stakeholders, production of language) were not as same as the author presented in Table 2. A revision is needed.\r\n3. Introduction, Lit Review and Methodology\r\nThe author began with a good introductory part giving background of the research topic to readers. The author established a good link between main points and then pointed to the research topic - ELT information on online newspapers.\r\nRegarding the related research, the author provided a brief review of previous research on ELT in the Thai context. Then the author addressed the research gap and point to the importance of this research.\r\nWith respect to methodological issues, the author gave a clear brief explanation of sources of data, instrument, data collection and data analysis. The   justification for selecting online newspaper, research instrument and types of analysis (word frequency, BNC, Log-likihood) is well-stated. However, the author should include the period of time  the 156 news reports were collected from (e.g. from year to year). Also, on page 3 line 4, there\'s a sentence which may confuse readers.  In the sentence beginning with \"Absolute frequencies of words in the corpus medical tourism news reports.....\" , should \'medical tourism\'  changed to \'ELT\'? \r\nAs for the results and discussion, the author presented the data logically and clearly using tables to facilitate readers. However, there\'s a minor error on language use. On page 4, line 4, a redundant phrase \'Thus, there is a need to \' should be deleted. The description for Table 2  should be revised as the frequencies and percentages of some themes were not as same as those presented in the table. For example, words relating to ELT and education matters should be \' f= 33; 46.48% \' instead of 31; 43.66%.  \r\nAs it is mentioned on page 1 that the findings of the study may illuminate some light on information regarding ELT practice in Thaialnd, it is suggested that the author may consider relating the results of corpus analysis to the findings of other studies to provide readers a clearer picture  / understanding of Thai ELT practice. By doing so, it can make a discussion part more meaningful.  Regarding the pedagogical implication for teaching English for Journalism, the author should devote a paragraph / part to explain more or giving some examples.\r\n\r\n4. Results and Discussion\r\nThe author restated his/her research objective, summarized key findings of the study pointing to areas of further research.\r\n5. Citations and References, and Formatting\r\nFor table three, themes must be numbered for ease of reference\r\nSome cited works not included in the reference list (Darasawang & Watson Todd, 2012; Scott & Tribble, 2006; Rayson, 2008; Rayson & Garside, 200)\r\nCheck format on citing references from online sources (date of retrieval before the URL)\r\n\r\nIMPORTANT: \r\nThe final draft should be uploaded to the conference website not later than 11 June 2019.\r\nThe author should send a file explaining how each of the comments has been addressed. See the attached file.\r\nThe author should send the revision note to any of the following emails:\r\nhcu.epc@gmail.com; jrc.hcu@gmail.com;','O-03-060.docx','O-03-060.docx',0),(162,167,430,NULL,NULL,NULL,481,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'DECISION: Accept with minor revision\r\n\r\n1. Please make sure that the citations match the references.\r\n2. Check that the manuscript is formatted according to the template provided by the committee.\r\n3. Formatting for the citations and references follows APA 6th edition.\r\n\r\nIMPORTANT: \r\nThe final draft should be uploaded to the conference website not later than Wednesday, 3rd  June 2019.',NULL,'O-03-061.docx',0),(163,168,430,NULL,NULL,NULL,446,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'DECISION: \r\nRESUBMIT for another round of double blind peer review\r\nPlease send directly your conceptual paper to jrc.hcu@gmail.com not later than the 7th of June 2019\r\n\r\nPlease kindly check the following comments to your submitted paper as guide for writing a NEW conceptual paper.\r\n1. Topic\r\nKindly check the title. The word \"on\" after the word \"performance\" is out of place.\r\n2. Abstract\r\nNo Abstract. The author must write the Abstract.\r\n3. Introduction, Lit Review and Methodology\r\nThe sections of the conceptual paper were not given titles. The reader was in quandary what the paragraphs were all about.\r\nThe author did not have a clear idea of what a conceptual paper is all about.\r\nBriefly, a conceptual paper is generally a review of related literature of a particular topic that is started by an introduction followed by the arguments (synthesized literature review) and summary of main points.\r\n1. Introduction. \r\n-This provides relevant context and background to the conceptual paper and the objective of the paper\r\n2. Content.\r\n-Synthesized literature review relevant to the objective(s) of the paper and the topic\r\ne.g. For the topic “Predictive Success in Criminology Licensure Examinations through Academic Performance: Implications on Program Development”, the Content (synthesized literature review should focus on:\r\n2.1 Discuss Predictive Success in Criminology Licensure Examinations and synthesize\r\n2.2 Discuss Literature review on predictive success in Criminology licensure examinations through academic performance and synthesize\r\n2.3 Discuss Literature review on implications of …. on Criminology program development and synthesize\r\n3. Summary\r\n-The author should present his/her stand on the literature review and identify which one of those presented is probably applicable to his/her own setting.\r\n5. Citations and References, and Formatting\r\nCitations MUST match the references',NULL,'O-03-062.docx',0),(164,169,476,NULL,NULL,NULL,430,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'DECISION: ACEEPT WITH REVISION\r\n1. Topic\r\nThe topic is clear and reflects the goal of the research study.\r\n2. Abstract\r\nThe abstract should be revised to include the findings.\r\nGrammar should be corrected.\r\n3. Introduction, Lit Review and Methodology\r\nThe author wrote \"Ecotourism ideally aims to have a low impact on the environment, contribute to the local economy, engender cross- cultural exchange and foster environmental education and in many ways, it has many advantages compared to tourism.\" The author is laying the foundation of the research, so citations are needed here.\r\nThe author wrote \"Ecotourism will always have significant positive or negative impacts on the social, economic and environmental dimensions of the host community, in general.\" What are some known +/- impacts. The author should unpack this a bit.\r\nThe author wrote \"Tangadan falls, situated within sitio Amontoc, Barangay Tangadan in the town of San Gabriel in La Union Province, is one of the ecotourism spots being popularized in the area and is very accessible for tourists and travelers visiting the surfing capital of the Philippines -- San Juan, La Union.\" What makes Tangadan Falls located in San Juan, La Union interesting to study? This information is crucial since there are hundreds of waterfalls in the area (of La Union and in the Philippines) and only one site was chosen by the researcher. The research should also unpack the context of the research. \r\nThe author wrote \"...there has been very little researches done on inland... Research in this context is uncountable.\r\n\"Further, the Millennium Ecosystem Assessment (MEA) in 2005 stated that they are among the most threatened ecosystems in the world.\" Include a reference.\r\n\"The collected macroinvertebrates were then studied under a microscope.\" Macroinvertebrates are visible to the naked eye. Why is there a need to use a microscope? What were studied under the microscope? This is OK but the author needs to unpack a bit the ‘goings on’.\r\n\"The instrument was divided into four parts namely: a.) Profile; b.) Knowledge; c.) Attitude; and d.) Practices.\" The reader is quite adamant on the validity of the instrument. The perceptions of stakeholders on the impacts of ecotourism were not asked. While it is plausible to generate insights from the responses of the participants in (c) and (d), directly asking the stakeholders of the impacts is more straightforward.\r\nThe title of the research study, \"Local Community Assessment on the Environmental Impacts of Ecotourism at Tangadan Falls, San Gabriel, La Union\" assumes that the locals are given the chance to assess the impacts of Ecotourism in the area. This was confirmed by the objective of the study, \"This study aims to identify the impacts of ecotourism within the Tangadan Falls ecosystem and recommend conservation measures that should be put in places before it becomes officially established tourist destination\". This objective is noble and worth examining. However, the instruments in gathering data (questionnaire) failed to gather data that shed light on the objectives.\r\nPut another way, the reader did not find these impacts in the manuscript. This is mainly due to faulty data gathering. Identifying the impacts using ocular investigation of biological biodiversity in the area is fine but the output or findings must be interpreted and synthesize  in a way that the impacts (+/-) stand out. The reader is left in quandary about what happened to the interview results. The impacts identified in the interview process (if any) are yet to be reported.\r\n3. Summary\r\nThe discussion and conclusion are very simplistic and do not give due justice to the objective of the study.\r\n4. Citations and References, and Formatting\r\nThere were a lot of grammatical inconsistencies. For instance, the author kept using \"based from\" instead of \"based on\". There several comma splices\r\nSome citations were not in the reference list and vice-versa.\r\nThe author should format the citations and references using APA 6th ed style.\r\nThe author should request an English language teacher or expert or a native English speaker to edit the language.\r\n\r\nIMPORTANT: \r\nThe final draft should be uploaded on the conference website not later than Wednesday,  13th  June 2019.\r\nThe author should send a file explaining how each of the comments has been addressed. See attached file.\r\nThe author should send the revision note to any of the following emails:\r\nhcu.epc@gmail.com; jrc.hcu@gmail.com','O-05-007.docx','O-05-007.docx',0),(165,170,430,NULL,NULL,NULL,482,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'DECISION: ACCEPT WITH MAJOR REVISION\r\n\r\nPlease check the attached file. A revision note template, the summary of comments of the peer reviewers and your reviewed draft will also be sent to the following email addresses:\r\nshinxhombrebueno@gmail.com, suratosdhan0812@gmail.com, besledjessa@gmail.com, and ellimactablada@gmail.com\r\n\r\nIMPORTANT: \r\nThe final draft should be uploaded to the conference website not later than Wednesday, 13th  of June 2019.\r\nThe author should send a file explaining how each of the comments has been addressed. See the attached file.\r\nThe author should send the revision note to any of the following emails: hcu.epc@gmail.com; jrc.hcu@gmail.com','O-03-063.docx','O-03-063.docx',0),(167,172,286,NULL,NULL,NULL,491,NULL,NULL,'O-01-025-2.docx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'Please send back the revised proceedings within : 14 June 2019 \r\nPlease check the file attachment\r\n\r\nEvaluation Criteria\r\n\r\nWater-Quality Assessment of Dipalo River in San Quintin, Pangasinan through Physico-chemical Parameters and Macrobenthos\r\n\r\nReviewer 1 \r\n1. Clarity of the topic\r\n    Comments and Suggestions : \r\n    1. It is interesting topic but it is not clarity of the results.\r\n   \r\n2. Well-written abstract that includes all salient point of the article\r\n    Comments and Suggestions : \r\n    1. Add the time of sampling collection in abstract.\r\n    2. Recheck some macroinvertebrates ex. Odontoceridae (it may be Hydropsychidae: in figure 1 (b))\r\n    3. Abstract: it should clarify relationship between water quality and macroinvertebrates.\r\n\r\n3. Introduction and sections that discusses the details of the article\r\n    Comments and Suggestions : \r\n    1. Add more information of Macrobenthos species used as bioindicators. \r\n    2. Results : put the table 1 under the contents. \r\n    3. Methodology and results : please  specify temperature in 2.0 Physico-chemical parameters and table 1 that you \r\n        measured ex. water / air  temperature.\r\n    4. Figure 1. you should put scale in your pictures. \r\n    5. Please recheck Figure 1. (b): it is not Odontoceridae. It should be Hydropsychidae. \r\n    6. Sampling sites are not clear in depth in upstream, midstream and downstream because the authors used surber \r\n        sampler to collect macrobenthos (suitable for less than 50 c. in depth) \r\n    7. Need to compare the results with other articles.\r\n\r\n4. Summary\r\n    Comments and Suggestions : \r\n    1. Explain more detail about the effect of water quality on macroinvertebrates and need to cites or compared with \r\n        other articles. (How do macroinvertebrates affect water quality?)\r\n\r\n5. Use of appropriate citation and references with correct format\r\n    Comments and Suggestions : \r\n    1. Check and follow reference from HCU Conference 2019. \r\n    2. The journal name, using full name or abbreviation according to HCU Conference 2019.\r\n\r\nReviewer 2\r\n1. Clarity of the topic\r\n    Comments and Suggestions : \r\n    1. It is very nice and interesting topic.\r\n   \r\n2. Well-written abstract that includes all salient point of the article\r\n    Comments and Suggestions : \r\n    1. It should explain or clarify relationship between water quality and macroinvertebrates.\r\n        Because it is the important content of this research. \r\n\r\n3. Introduction and sections that discusses the details of the article\r\n    Comments and Suggestions : \r\n    1. Please check the format of table according to the guildline\'s HCU conference.\r\n    2. Give more information of Macrobenthos species used as bioindicators to increase the important academic \r\n        content.\r\n\r\n4. Summary\r\n    Comments and Suggestions : \r\n    1. Please give more detail about the effect of water quality on macroinvertebrates.\r\n\r\n5. Use of appropriate citation and references with correct format\r\n    Comments and Suggestions : \r\n    1. Check the format of reference according to the guildline\'s HCU conference.','O-01-025.pdf','O-01-025.docx',0),(168,173,430,NULL,NULL,NULL,451,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'1. The author provided a clear introduction with measurable objectives.\r\n\r\n2. The review of related studies was quite limited despite the fact that \"Reading Literacy\" and \"Predictors of Achievement\" are commonly examined in the field. It is highly suggested that this section be enriched.\r\n3. Results were taken directly from the output of the FDG.\r\n4. There was only very minimal attempt to discuss and synthesize the findings. Qualitative research enterprises are aimed at digging in-depth insights. One way direct way to do this is to present the research results, synthesizing them and relating to existing literature. The author presented the research results and provided very minimal discussions. There was no attempt to relate the findings to any existing literature on \"Reading Literacy\" and \"Predictors of Achievement\" or Reading Literacy as Predictors of Achievement. This can be due partly to unsubstantial review of related research.\r\n\r\n4. Please check that the citations match the references.\r\n\r\nIMPORTANT: \r\nThe final draft should be uploaded to the conference website not later than 3 June 2019.\r\nThe author should send a file explaining how each of the comments has been addressed. See the attached file.\r\nThe author should send the revision note to any of the following emails:\r\nhcu.epc@gmail.com; jrc.hcu@gmail.com;','O-03-065.docx','O-03-065.docx',0),(169,174,227,NULL,NULL,NULL,484,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,'DECISION: RESUBMIT \r\nNOTE: Resubmitted papers should reach the editorial not later than Friday, 12th June 2019, so they can be included in another round of double blind peer review process.\r\n\r\nComment/Suggestions:\r\n\r\nThis is NOT yet a conceptual paper. \r\nIn a conceptual paper, the following should be vividly included: \r\n\r\nAbstract\r\nKeywords\r\n\r\n1. Introduction. This section provides a clear background and context of the paper that leads to the objective(s). The context is important as it provides boundaries of the paper (e.g. HAU K-12 students)\r\n\r\n2. Concepts and Arguments\r\n2.1 Whole Child Approach (WCA) Concept\r\n-Explain the concepts and main arguments in WCA\r\n-Include credible references of related research\r\n2.2 Comer School Development Program (CSDP)\r\n-Explain the concepts and main arguments in CSDP\r\n--Include credible references of related research\r\n\r\n3. Discussion and Synthesis\r\n3.1 Addressing the low academic performance of students\r\n-Discuss how the interface of the of WCA and CSDP may address the decreasing academic performance of students.\r\n-Draw arguments from 